assay_description: Antiviral activity against HCoV-229E infected in human MRC5 cells incubated for 2 hrs by XTT method
Antiviral activity against recombinant HCoV-229E infected in MRC5 cells assessed as inhibition of plaque formation incubated upto 3 days by crystal violet staining based plaque-reduction assay
Antiviral activity against HCoV-229E assessed as reduction of viral RNA level at 4 uM

Antiviral activity against HCoV-229E harboring luciferase reporter gene infected in human Huh-7 cells assessed as reduction in viral replication pre-incubated for 1 hrs followed by replacement with fresh media for 6 hrs by renilla luciferase based luminometer analysis
